# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Open-core snapshot exclusions (b4m-infra#507).
#
# `export-ignore` tells `git archive` to OMIT these paths. The open-core launch
# cuts the public repo via `git archive HEAD`, so anything marked here does not
# ship in the snapshot. This is the documented, in-tree BACKSTOP; the cut script
# (scratchpad/cut-snapshot.sh) also rm's the same set as a second pass, and a
# recon/secret scan gates the cut. `export-ignore` only affects `git archive`
# (not a plain clone/copy), which is exactly the snapshot mechanism.
#
# Validated by scripts/check-export-ignore.sh (asserts every entry below is
# absent from `git archive HEAD`). Keep this list in sync with that script and
# with scratchpad/cut-snapshot.sh.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# NOTE: dead-client / live-served docs are DELETED outright (PR #9805), not
# export-ignore'd — a customer-deployment DB doc, apps/client/public/docs/roadmap/,
# an internal infosec package, and an internal SVG design-system doc. cut-snapshot.sh
# keeps a guarded `rm` for them as a belt.

# NOTE: the internal working-docs tree (top-level docs/, formerly export-ignored
# here) and rawScreenshots/ were moved OUT of the repo entirely for the freeze —
# archived to the private cpo repo (cpo/lumina5-archive/), along with
# the OptiHashi overlay's {VISION,IDEATION,EXTRACTION,BUILD_PLAN}.md and two stray
# internal plan docs. Physically absent, so no export-ignore entry is needed.

# ── docs-site — the Docusaurus source for docs.bike4mind.com, excluded WHOLESALE ──
# The published docs site is internal-heavy (security control objectives, AWS
# onboarding/process runbooks, DocumentDB solution summaries, and the internal
# roadmap that names a customer + @milliononmars.com emails). Rather than
# triage it page-by-page, the whole tree is dropped from the public snapshot.
# This is SNAPSHOT-ONLY: `export-ignore` affects `git archive` alone (not the
# working tree, not any clone/copy), and `git archive` runs nowhere in lumina5's
# CI/deploy/build — so docs.bike4mind.com keeps deploying from lumina5 exactly as
# today, untouched. docs-site is also excluded from the pnpm workspace
# (pnpm-workspace.yaml `- '!docs-site'`, zero lockfile refs), so dropping it does
# not affect `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` on the snapshot. This supersedes
# the narrower per-page and roadmap/ entries from #9748/#9909. The standalone
# docs-deploy workflow is excluded too (below). _verify-docs-build.yml is NOT
# excluded: deploy.yml `uses:` it as a local reusable workflow, and GitHub
# resolves that reference at trigger time even when the job's `if:` is false —
# export-ignoring it makes every deploy.yml run on the snapshot repo fail at
# 0s with "workflow file issue". It ships instead; its canonical-repo guard
# (vars.CANONICAL_REPO) keeps the docs job permanently skipped off-repo.
docs-site/** export-ignore
.github/workflows/deploy-docs.yml export-ignore
# ── EXCEPT the in-app help corpus ───────────────────────────────────────────
# The Help Panel's articles ARE docs-site/docs/{features,admin} — loadHelpArticles.ts
# reads them, and two CI gates (helpContentRendering.test.tsx, help-corpus-
# validation.test.ts) fail on an empty corpus, which is exactly what the wholesale
# exclusion shipped. Carve the two category trees back in (later lines win), then
# re-exclude the loader's own EXCLUDED_FILES + quest-examples — internal
# design/roadmap/plan docs parked in the category dirs that the loader never
# serves (three carry flavor text from the hard-blocked identity set).
# Keep this list in sync with EXCLUDED_FILES/EXCLUDED_DIRS in
# packages/scripts/help/loadHelpArticles.ts.
#
# Directory-prune gotcha: `git archive` does NOT descend into an export-ignored
# directory, so a file-level `-export-ignore` under `docs-site/**` alone never
# gets consulted. Un-ignore each intermediate directory, then re-ignore its
# contents, then carve the kept subtrees back in (last matching line wins).
docs-site/docs -export-ignore
docs-site/docs/** export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features -export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/** -export-ignore
docs-site/docs/admin -export-ignore
docs-site/docs/admin/** -export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/to-do.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/system-secrets-management.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/research-mode-implementation.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/notebook-splash-design.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/notebook-import-export.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/gamedev-powered-roadmap.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/artifacts-system-roadmap.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/feature-flags.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/questmaster-export.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/admin/accounts.md export-ignore
docs-site/docs/features/quest-examples/** export-ignore

